Figma

Vertical auto-layout

Padding: space-10

Gap: space-8

React
export function PageContainer({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
  return (
    <main className="flex flex-col gap-8 p-10 bg-bg-primary min-h-screen">
      {children}
    </main>
  );
}

2.5 Card
Figma

Padding: space-5

Gap: space-4

React
export function Card({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
  return (
    <section className="flex flex-col gap-4 p-5 bg-bg-secondary border border-border-default rounded-lg">
      {children}
    </section>
  );
}

2.6 FormGroup
Figma

Vertical auto-layout

Gap: space-2

React
export function FormGroup({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
  return <div className="flex flex-col gap-2">{children}</div>;
}

2.7 Mobile Bottom Navigation
Figma

Height: 56px

Icon gap: space-1

React
export function MobileNav() {
  return (
    <nav className="fixed bottom-0 inset-x-0 h-14 bg-bg-primary border-t border-border-default flex justify-around items-center">
      <button className="flex flex-col items-center gap-1 text-xs">Crew</button>
      <button className="flex flex-col items-center gap-1 text-xs">QR</button>
      <button className="flex flex-col items-center gap-1 text-xs">Log</button>
      <button className="flex flex-col items-center gap-1 text-xs">Incident</button>
    </nav>
  );
}

3. ENFORCEMENT RULES (UI + TAILWIND)

These are non-negotiable:

❌ No className="p-[18px]"

❌ No inline margin-top hacks

❌ No visual-only spacing adjustments

✅ All spacing must map to spacing tokens

✅ Figma spacing token == Tailwind spacing value

If it doesn’t map, it doesn’t ship.

FINAL CONFIRMATION

You now have:

✅ Tailwind config fully mapped to Figma tokens

✅ React components aligned to auto-layout rules

✅ Zero divergence between design and code

✅ UI that scales with real data and audits

This is enterprise UI infrastructure, not theme work.
